Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

This does conform to required minimum deprecation period, per governance [1] and seeing as it is not a major feature I can see potentially accepting this removal but it feels like the sort of thing I would prefer to at least put off until the beginning of Queens.

I have not looked more carefully to see if there is another reason to rush this. I could be convinced to go the other way.

[1] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/tags/assert_follows-standard-deprecation.html

Steve, I do not have any specific reason to rush this. Just followed the usual deprecation policy and was attempting a clean up.
Having this around opens up a slight possibility of the response header that is set by the oslo middleware to be modified. That could be a good reason to get rid of it maybe?

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

It's fine to remove. It *is* in 2 stable branches now. It just looks like it went in later in Newton, and Ocata was a short cycle in terms of time so I was being squeamish.
